sequenceDiagram
    participant User as User/Dashboard
    participant K8sAPI as Kubernetes API Server<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS1.3
    participant Webhook as ODH Notebook Webhook<br/>8443/TCP HTTPS mTLS
    participant ImageAPI as ImageStream API<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS1.2+
    participant Controller as ODH Notebook Controller<br/>Watch Loop
    participant Router as OpenShift Router<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS1.3
    participant OAuthProxy as OAuth Proxy Sidecar<br/>8443/TCP HTTPS TLS1.2+
    participant OAuthServer as OpenShift OAuth Server<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS1.2+
    participant Notebook as Jupyter Notebook<br/>8888/TCP HTTP

    Note over User,Notebook: Flow 1: Notebook Creation with OAuth Injection

    User->>K8sAPI: POST Notebook CR<br/>Auth: Bearer Token
    K8sAPI->>Webhook: Mutating Webhook<br/>mTLS (Service CA)
    Webhook->>ImageAPI: Resolve ImageStream<br/>ServiceAccount Token
    ImageAPI-->>Webhook: Image Reference
    Webhook->>Webhook: Inject OAuth Proxy Sidecar<br/>Mount CA Bundle
    Webhook-->>K8sAPI: Mutated Notebook Spec
    K8sAPI-->>User: Notebook Created

    K8sAPI->>Controller: Watch Event<br/>Notebook Created
    Controller->>K8sAPI: Create ServiceAccount<br/>ServiceAccount Token
    Controller->>K8sAPI: Create Service<br/>ServiceAccount Token
    Controller->>K8sAPI: Create Secret (OAuth Config)<br/>ServiceAccount Token
    Controller->>K8sAPI: Create Route (TLS Reencrypt)<br/>ServiceAccount Token
    Controller->>K8sAPI: Create NetworkPolicies<br/>ServiceAccount Token
    Controller->>K8sAPI: Create CA Bundle ConfigMap<br/>ServiceAccount Token

    Note over User,Notebook: Flow 2: User Accessing OAuth-Protected Notebook

    User->>Router: HTTPS Request<br/>443/TCP TLS 1.3
    Router->>OAuthProxy: Forward Request<br/>8443/TCP TLS 1.2+ (Reencrypt)

    alt User Not Authenticated
        OAuthProxy->>OAuthServer: OAuth Flow Redirect<br/>443/TCP HTTPS
        OAuthServer-->>User: Login Page
        User->>OAuthServer: Credentials
        OAuthServer-->>OAuthProxy: OAuth Token
    end

    OAuthProxy->>K8sAPI: SubjectAccessReview (SAR)<br/>Verify: get notebooks/{name}<br/>ServiceAccount Token
    K8sAPI-->>OAuthProxy: Authorized: true

    OAuthProxy->>Notebook: Forward Request<br/>8888/TCP HTTP (localhost)
    Notebook-->>OAuthProxy: Jupyter Response
    OAuthProxy-->>Router: HTTPS Response<br/>8443/TCP TLS 1.2+
    Router-->>User: HTTPS Response<br/>443/TCP TLS 1.3

    Note over User,Notebook: Flow 3: CA Certificate Bundle Management

    Controller->>K8sAPI: Watch ConfigMap<br/>odh-trusted-ca-bundle
    K8sAPI-->>Controller: ConfigMap Updated
    Controller->>K8sAPI: Get kube-root-ca.crt<br/>ServiceAccount Token
    Controller->>Controller: Merge CA Certificates
    Controller->>K8sAPI: Create/Update<br/>workbench-trusted-ca-bundle<br/>ServiceAccount Token
    Controller->>K8sAPI: Patch Notebook<br/>Add VolumeMount & Env Vars
    K8sAPI->>Notebook: Mount CA Bundle<br/>Set PIP_CERT, REQUESTS_CA_BUNDLE, etc.
